er window of at least 4 hours for final migration and DNS/connection string switchover", "All 10 SQL Agent jobs use T-SQL or supported subsystems compatible with Azure SQL MI (e.g., no CmdExec steps requiring OS-level access)", "Database does not rely on unsupported SQL Server features such as cross-database queries, CLR assemblies requiring unsafe permissions, or Service Broker requiring external activation"], "deliverables": ["Fully migrated and operational 100GB database on Azure SQL Managed Instance with validated data integrity", "10 SQL Agent jobs recreated and verified on Azure SQL MI with documented job configuration details", "Migration summary report including pre/post object counts, compatibility findings, and any remediation steps applied", "Azure SQL MI connection string details and updated endpoint documentation for application teams", "Post-migration sign-off checklist confirming validation tests passed for schema, data, jobs, and user access"], "out_of_scope": ["Application code changes or re-development of client applications connecting to the database", "Networking infrastructure setup beyond Azure SQL MI public or private endpoint configuration", "Migration of additional databases not specified in this engagement", "Ongoing Azure SQL MI management, monitoring, or administration post-migration", "Azure cost optimisation, reserved instance purchasing, or licensing advisory", "SSIS packages, SSRS reports, or linked server re-configuration to third-party systems"], "prerequisites": ["Valid Azure subscription credentials and Owner or Contributor role access granted to the migration engineer", "SQL Server sysadmin credentials for the source SQL Server 2019 instance", "Network connectivity confirmed between source environment and target Azure SQL MI (VNet peering, VPN, or ExpressRoute)", "DMA or Azure DMS pre-assessment report shared prior to engagement start, or time allocated within scope for assessment"], "timeline_days": 12, "milestone_count": 1}	1	2