cmnsl5siv0000m0tvyvq7xye6	cmnogbz5500040ctvk0h77tjv	I need to migrate sql server 2019 database to Azure MI , Database size is 100G, 10 users, 10 SQL agent jobs,	null	DATABASE	COMPLETE	9	0	\N	```json\n{\n  "title": "SQL Server 2019 to Azure SQL Managed Instance Migration — 100GB Database",\n  "domain": "DATABASE",\n  "objective": "Migrate a 100GB SQL Server 2019 on-premises database to Azure SQL Managed Instance (MI), ensuring full fidelity of schema, data, stored procedures, SQL Agent jobs, logins, and linked server configurations, with minimal downtime and validated post-migration functionality for 10 users and 10 SQL Agent jobs.",\n  "in_scope": [\n    "Pre-migration assessment using Data Migration Assistant (DMA) or Azure Database Migration Service (DMS) to identify compatibility issues",\n    "Provisioning and configuration of Azure SQL Managed Instance (General Purpose or Business Critical tier as agreed)",\n    "Migration of the 100GB database including all schema objects, tables, indexes, views, stored procedures, functions, and triggers",\n    "Migration and recreation of 10 SQL Agent jobs with validation of job steps, schedules, and operators",\n    "Migration of SQL Server logins, users, roles, and permission assignments to Azure SQL MI",\n    "Execution of full backup/restore or online migration using Azure Database Migration Service with cutover coordination",\n    "Post-migration validation including row count checks, object integrity verification, and SQL Agent job test execution",\n    "Update of connection strings and documentation of new Azure SQL MI endpoint details for client handover"\n  ],\n  "out_of_scope": [\n    "Application code changes or re-development of client applications connecting to the database",\n    "Networking infrastructure setup beyond Azure SQL MI public or private endpoint configuration",\n    "Migration of additional databases not specified in this engagement",\n    "Ongoing Azure SQL MI management, monitoring, or administration post-migration",\n    "Azure cost optimisation, reserved instance purchasing, or licensing advisory",\n    "SSIS packages, SSRS reports, or linked server re-configuration to third-party systems"\n  ],\n  "assumptions": [\n    "Customer holds valid Azure subscription with sufficient quota to provision an Azure SQL Managed Instance in the desired region",\n    "Source SQL Server 2019 instance is accessible to the migration engineer via VPN, Azure ExpressRoute, or direct network connectivity",\n    "Customer has an approved maintenance or cutover window of at least 4 hours for final migration and DNS/connection string switchover",\n    "All 10 SQL Agent jobs use T-SQL or supported subsystems compatible with Azure SQL MI (e.g., no CmdExec steps requiring OS-level access)",\n    "Database does not rely on unsupported SQL Server features such as cross-database queries, CLR assemblies requiring unsafe permissions, or Service Broker requiring external activation"\n  ],\n  "prerequisites": [\n    "Valid Azure subscription credentials and Owner or Contributor role access granted to the migration engineer",\n    "SQL Server sysadmin credentials for the source SQL Server 2019 instance",\n    "Network connectivity confirmed between source environment and target Azure SQL MI (VNet peering, VPN, or ExpressRoute)",\n    "DMA or Azure DMS pre-assessment report shared prior to engagement start, or time allocated within scope for assessment"\n  ],\n  "deliverables": [\n    "Fully migrated and operational 100GB database on Azure SQL Managed Instance with validated data integrity",\n    "10 SQL Agent jobs recreated and verified on Azure SQL MI with documented job configuration details",\n    "Migration summary report including pre/post object counts, compatibility findings, and any remediation steps applied",\n    "Azure SQL MI connection string details and updated endpoint documentation for application teams",\n    "Post-migration sign-off checklist confirming validation tests passed for schema, data, jobs, and user access"\n  ],\n  "currency": "AUD",\n  "price": 3200,\n  "hours_min": 16,\n  "hours_max": 30,\n  "milestone_count": 1\n}\n```	{"price": 3200, "title": "SQL Server 2019 to Azure SQL Managed Instance Migration — 100GB Database", "domain": "DATABASE", "currency": "AUD", "in_scope": ["Pre-migration assessment using Data Migration Assistant (DMA) or Azure Database Migration Service (DMS) to identify compatibility issues", "Provisioning and configuration of Azure SQL Managed Instance (General Purpose or Business Critical tier as agreed)", "Migration of the 100GB database including all schema objects, tables, indexes, views, stored procedures, functions, and triggers", "Migration and recreation of 10 SQL Agent jobs with validation of job steps, schedules, and operators", "Migration of SQL Server logins, users, roles, and permission assignments to Azure SQL MI", "Execution of full backup/restore or online migration using Azure Database Migration Service with cutover coordination", "Post-migration validation including row count checks, object integrity verification, and SQL Agent job test execution", "Update of connection strings and documentation of new Azure SQL MI endpoint details for client handover"], "hours_max": 30, "hours_min": 16, "objective": "Migrate a 100GB SQL Server 2019 on-premises database to Azure SQL Managed Instance (MI), ensuring full fidelity of schema, data, stored procedures, SQL Agent jobs, logins, and linked server configurations, with minimal downtime and validated post-migration functionality for 10 users and 10 SQL Agent jobs.", "assumptions": ["Customer holds valid Azure subscription with sufficient quota to provision an Azure SQL Managed Instance in the desired region", "Source SQL Server 2019 instance is accessible to the migration engineer via VPN, Azure ExpressRoute, or direct network connectivity", "Customer has an approved maintenance or cutover window of at least 4 hours for final migration and DNS/connection string switchover", "All 10 SQL Agent jobs use T-SQL or supported subsystems compatible with Azure SQL MI (e.g., no CmdExec steps requiring OS-level access)", "Database does not rely on unsupported SQL Server features such as cross-database queries, CLR assemblies requiring unsafe permissions, or Service Broker requiring external activation"], "deliverables": ["Fully migrated and operational 100GB database on Azure SQL Managed Instance with validated data integrity", "10 SQL Agent jobs recreated and verified on Azure SQL MI with documented job configuration details", "Migration summary report including pre/post object counts, compatibility findings, and any remediation steps applied", "Azure SQL MI connection string details and updated endpoint documentation for application teams", "Post-migration sign-off checklist confirming validation tests passed for schema, data, jobs, and user access"], "out_of_scope": ["Application code changes or re-development of client applications connecting to the database", "Networking infrastructure setup beyond Azure SQL MI public or private endpoint configuration", "Migration of additional databases not specified in this engagement", "Ongoing Azure SQL MI management, monitoring, or administration post-migration", "Azure cost optimisation, reserved instance purchasing, or licensing advisory", "SSIS packages, SSRS reports, or linked server re-configuration to third-party systems"], "prerequisites": ["Valid Azure subscription credentials and Owner or Contributor role access granted to the migration engineer", "SQL Server sysadmin credentials for the source SQL Server 2019 instance", "Network connectivity confirmed between source environment and target Azure SQL MI (VNet peering, VPN, or ExpressRoute)", "DMA or Azure DMS pre-assessment report shared prior to engagement start, or time allocated within scope for assessment"], "milestone_count": 1}	{"price": 3200, "title": "SQL Server 2019 to Azure SQL Managed Instance Migration — 100GB Database", "domain": "DATABASE", "currency": "AUD", "in_scope": ["Pre-migration assessment using Data Migration Assistant (DMA) or Azure Database Migration Service (DMS) to identify compatibility issues", "Provisioning and configuration of Azure SQL Managed Instance (General Purpose or Business Critical tier as agreed)", "Migration of the 100GB database including all schema objects, tables, indexes, views, stored procedures, functions, and triggers", "Migration and recreation of 10 SQL Agent jobs with validation of job steps, schedules, and operators", "Migration of SQL Server logins, users, roles, and permission assignments to Azure SQL MI", "Execution of full backup/restore or online migration using Azure Database Migration Service with cutover coordination", "Post-migration validation including row count checks, object integrity verification, and SQL Agent job test execution", "Update of connection strings and documentation of new Azure SQL MI endpoint details for client handover"], "hours_max": 30, "hours_min": 16, "objective": "Migrate a 100GB SQL Server 2019 on-premises database to Azure SQL Managed Instance (MI), ensuring full fidelity of schema, data, stored procedures, SQL Agent jobs, logins, and linked server configurations, with minimal downtime and validated post-migration functionality for 10 users and 10 SQL Agent jobs.", "assumptions": ["Customer holds valid Azure subscription with sufficient quota to provision an Azure SQL Managed Instance in the desired region", "Source SQL Server 2019 instance is accessible to the migration engineer via VPN, Azure ExpressRoute, or direct network connectivity", "Customer has an approved maintenance or cutover window of at least 4 hours for final migration and DNS/connection string switchover", "All 10 SQL Agent jobs use T-SQL or supported subsystems compatible with Azure SQL MI (e.g., no CmdExec steps requiring OS-level access)", "Database does not rely on unsupported SQL Server features such as cross-database queries, CLR assemblies requiring unsafe permissions, or Service Broker requiring external activation"], "deliverables": ["Fully migrated and operational 100GB database on Azure SQL Managed Instance with validated data integrity", "10 SQL Agent jobs recreated and verified on Azure SQL MI with documented job configuration details", "Migration summary report including pre/post object counts, compatibility findings, and any remediation steps applied", "Azure SQL MI connection string details and updated endpoint documentation for application teams", "Post-migration sign-off checklist confirming validation tests passed for schema, data, jobs, and user access"], "out_of_scope": ["Application code changes or re-development of client applications connecting to the database", "Networking infrastructure setup beyond Azure SQL MI public or private endpoint configuration", "Migration of additional databases not specified in this engagement", "Ongoing Azure SQL MI management, monitoring, or administration post-migration", "Azure cost optimisation, reserved instance purchasing, or licensing advisory", "SSIS packages, SSRS reports, or linked server re-configuration to third-party systems"], "prerequisites": ["Valid Azure subscription credentials and Owner or Contributor role access granted to the migration engineer", "SQL Server sysadmin credentials for the source SQL Server 2019 instance", "Network connectivity confirmed between source environment and target Azure SQL MI (VNet peering, VPN, or ExpressRoute)", "DMA or Azure DMS pre-assessment report shared prior to engagement start, or time allocated within scope for assessment"], "milestone_count": 1}	f	{}	[]	2026-04-10 07:31:04.949	\N	2026-04-10 07:29:58.951	2026-04-10 07:31:04.952
cmnsrllqr000eectv80osq7up	cmnogbz5500040ctvk0h77tjv	Upgrade SQL Server 2008R2 to SQL Server 2019	null	DATABASE	COMPLETE	10	0	\N	{\n  "title": "SQL Server 2008 R2 to SQL Server 2019 In-Place or Migration Upgrade",\n  "domain": "DATABASE",\n  "objective": "Upgrade the existing SQL Server 2008 R2 instance to SQL Server 2019, ensuring all databases, logins, jobs, linked servers, and configuration settings are successfully migrated with minimal downtime, validated data integrity, and compatibility levels adjusted to SQL Server 2019 standards.",\n  "in_scope": [\n    "Pre-upgrade assessment of existing SQL Server 2008 R2 instance using Microsoft Upgrade Advisor or Database Experimentation Assistant (DEA)",\n    "Full backup of all user databases, system databases, SQL Agent jobs, and server-level objects prior to any upgrade activity",\n    "Installation and configuration of SQL Server 2019 on target server (in-place upgrade or new instance migration)",\n    "Migration of all user databases, logins, roles, permissions, linked servers, and SQL Agent jobs to SQL Server 2019",\n    "Database compatibility level review and adjustment to SQL Server 2019 (150) where appropriate",\n    "Post-upgrade validation including database integrity checks (DBCC CHECKDB), login verification, and job execution testing",\n    "Update of database connection strings and application configuration files where access is provided",\n    "Documented rollback procedure and execution support in the event of a critical upgrade failure"\n  ],\n  "out_of_scope": [\n    "Application code changes, stored procedure rewrites, or query refactoring to address deprecated feature incompatibilities",\n    "Operating system upgrades or Windows Server migration",\n    "SQL Server licensing procurement or Microsoft volume licensing management",\n    "Network infrastructure changes or firewall rule modifications",\n    "Third-party application vendor support or coordination",\n    "Ongoing SQL Server performance tuning or DBA managed services post-upgrade"\n  ],\n  "assumptions": [\n    "Customer has valid SQL Server 2019 license and installation media available prior to engagement start",\n    "Customer can provide a scheduled maintenance window of sufficient duration to complete the upgrade with acceptable downtime",\n    "Existing SQL Server 2008 R2 instance is on hardware or a VM that meets SQL Server 2019 minimum system requirements",\n    "Customer has administrative access to the host operating system and SQL Server instance",\n    "All dependent applications and services are owned or accessible by the customer for post-upgrade connectivity testing"\n  ],\n  "prerequisites": [\n    "Full verified backup of all SQL Server 2008 R2 databases and server-level objects completed and stored offsite or on separate media",\n    "SQL Server 2019 installation media and valid product license key provided by the customer",\n    "Remote or on-site access credentials for the target server with local administrator and sysadmin SQL privileges",\n    "Inventory list of all databases, applications, and services connecting to the SQL Server instance"\n  ],\n  "deliverables": [\n    "Pre-upgrade assessment report detailing deprecated features, compatibility risks, and recommended remediation steps",\n    "Fully operational SQL Server 2019 instance with all databases, logins, jobs, and linked servers successfully migrated",\n    "Post-upgrade validation report confirming DBCC CHECKDB results, login integrity, and SQL Agent job status",\n    "Rollback procedure document outlining steps to restore SQL Server 2008 R2 environment if required",\n    "Upgrade summary handover document including configuration changes, compatibility level settings, and recommendations for ongoing maintenance"\n  ],\n  "currency": "AUD",\n  "price": 2400,\n  "hours_min": 8,\n  "hours_max": 20,\n  "milestone_count": 1\n}	{"price": 2400, "title": "SQL Server 2008 R2 to SQL Server 2019 In-Place or Migration Upgrade", "d