cmnsv1fzw0008i4tvoek2grzb	cmnogbz5500040ctvk0h77tjv	Add firewall rule to the firewall for outgoing internet traffic	null	FIREWALL	COMPLETE	11	0	\N	{\n  "title": "Firewall Outbound Internet Traffic Rule Configuration",\n  "domain": "FIREWALL",\n  "objective": "Configure and implement a specific outbound internet traffic firewall rule to control, permit, or restrict egress traffic from the internal network to the internet, ensuring the rule is correctly defined, tested, and documented in accordance with the organisation's security policy.",\n  "in_scope": [\n    "Review of existing firewall ruleset and outbound traffic policy",\n    "Definition of rule parameters including source zone, destination zone, port, protocol, and action",\n    "Creation and insertion of the outbound internet traffic rule in the correct policy order",\n    "Verification that the rule functions as intended using live traffic or connection testing",\n    "Review for rule conflicts or unintended policy bypass introduced by the new rule",\n    "Documentation of the new rule including purpose, owner, and date of implementation"\n  ],\n  "out_of_scope": [\n    "Changes to inbound or NAT firewall rules",\n    "Firewall firmware or software upgrades",\n    "Full firewall policy audit or security hardening",\n    "Network topology redesign or re-addressing",\n    "Configuration of proxy, content filtering, or web gateway services",\n    "Ongoing firewall management or monitoring after rule implementation"\n  ],\n  "assumptions": [\n    "Customer has administrative access to the firewall management interface",\n    "The firewall make, model, and current software version are supported and functional",\n    "The customer can clearly define the source, destination, port, and protocol requirements for the rule",\n    "A maintenance window is available to apply and test the change with minimal business disruption"\n  ],\n  "prerequisites": [\n    "Administrative credentials or authorised access for the assi