ings including memory allocation, tempdb optimisation, and authentication mode", "Apply SQL Server security hardening including sa account management, surface area configuration, and Windows Firewall rules", "Configure automated SQL Server backup jobs using SQL Server Agent covering full, differential, and transaction log backups", "Set up Azure Blob Storage as the backup destination for offsite retention of database backup files", "Validate the installation and backup solution via test backup and restore operation with documented results"], "hours_max": 12, "hours_min": 6, "objective": "Deploy a fully configured Microsoft SQL Server 2019 instance on an Azure-hosted Windows Server virtual machine, including instance configuration, security hardening, and an automated backup solution to ensure data protection and recoverability in a production-grade Azure environment.", "assumptions": ["Customer holds an active Azure subscription with sufficient quota and permissions to provision virtual machines and storage accounts", "Customer has a valid SQL Server 2019 licence or is eligible for Azure Hybrid Benefit; licensing cost is not included in this engagement", "The Azure VM size and storage tier will be selected to meet the customer's stated workload requirements prior to provisioning", "Remote access to the Azure VM via RDP or Azure Bastion will be available to the engineer throughout the engagement", "Customer accepts that backup retention policy and schedule will be defined and agreed upon before implementation begins"], "deliverables": ["Fully installed and configured SQL Server 2019 instance running on an Azure Windows Server VM", "Automated backup jobs configured in SQL Server Agent with full, differential, and transaction log schedules targeting Azure Blob Storage", "Post-installation configuration document detailing instance settings, service accounts, firewall rules, and backup policy", "Evidence of a successful test backup and restore operation confirming backup